    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, if the data shows that rehabilitation and social stuff works better, then doesn't that basically mean the \"tough on crime\" approach is just wrong? like, isn't it kind of disingenuous to keep calling it a \"debate\" if one side is clearly backed by the data and the other is just... well, outdated?",
