      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While data strongly supports the benefits of rehabilitative and social interventions, labeling the \"tough on crime\" approach as entirely \"wrong\" is an oversimplification of the political reality. Proponents of punitive measures often argue that deterrence, incapacitation, and strict penalties are necessary components alongside social programs. The perceived \"debate\" often reflects a conflict between empirical data favoring preventative approaches and strong public desire for visible, immediate punitive action.",
